description.narrative: UNICEF supported the Government of Tajikistan in putting in place a better social protection system to address the needs of the most vulnerable children, including children affected by emergencies, affected by migration and children with disabilities. To reach out to most vulnerable children and ensure their access to fundamental services, UNICEF supported over 3,500 children affected by migration to access social welfare services in 14 districts. Over 2,400 children obtained birth certificates. Implementation of the five-year communication for social change on social inclusion of persons with disabilities in collaboration with MoHSPP is in progress. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/12/2019
